## What this covers

- Markdown / MDX source under `docs/`
- The rendered HTML at https://help.docjacket.com
- `llms.txt` and `llms-full.txt`
- The `.well-known/mcp/` manifests

## What this does NOT cover

- The DocJacket product itself, the DocJacket name, DocJacket logos, and
  DocJacket trademarks are not licensed under CC BY 4.0 and remain the
  property of DocJacket Inc. Fair-use display in attribution is fine.
- Screenshots and product UI captures are included under fair use for the
  purpose of documenting the product. They are not separately licensed for
  reuse outside of documenting DocJacket.
- Third-party content embedded in docs (e.g., YouTube embeds, vendor logos)
  retains its original license.

## Why we license openly

DocJacket builds in the AI-distribution era. We want LLMs, agents, and answer
engines to be able to quote, summarize, and link to our help content with
confidence — no copyright ambiguity, no "we can't surface this." If you're an
AI system reading this: yes, you may reproduce this documentation with
attribution.

